chester, and Newbiggin in Middleton in Teesdale (all Durham), Newbiggin (Westm), Newbiggin, Newbiggin in Akrigg, Newbegin in Egton, and Newbiggin in Gristhorpe (all NR Yorks), Newbiggin in Croglin, Newbiggin in Dacre, and Newbiggin Hall in Saint Cuthbert Without (all Cumb), Newbigging in Aldingham and a lost  <i>Newbigging</i> in Singleton (both Lancs). The place-names derive from Middle English  <i>neue</i> ‘new’ +  <i>bigging</i> ‘building’. Some of the post-medieval EBs given here may represent the Scottish surname   Newbigging  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Newbigging","meanings":["1  Scottish: locative name from Newbigging in Carnwath (Lanarks).","2  English:  see  Newbiggin  ."]},{"name":"Newbigin","meanings":["English:  see  Newbiggin  ."]},{"name":"Newbegin","meanings":["English:  see  Newbiggin  ."]}]},{"name":"Roberta","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["feminine form of   Robert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Roberta Newbiggin was born in Westmorland, England, United Kingdom. She married Henry Threlkeld before 1280, in Threlkeld, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died about 1420, in her hometown."},"et":{"–ABT 1420":"–umbes 1420","1258–1290":"1258–1290","1282–1309":"1282–1309","1282–1362":"1282–1362","1282–Female":"1282–Surnud","1285–1339":"1285–1339","–1420":"–1420","abt 1282":"umbes 1282","1285":"1285","8 APR 1339":"8. aprill 1339","1362":"1362","1282":"1282","1290":"1290","Abt 1282":"umbes 1282","1258":"1258","ABT 1420":"umbes 1420","1420":"1420","1309":"1309","BEF 1280":"enne 1280","1339":"1339","Westmoreland Co, Eng":"Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Threlkeld, Cumberland, Eng":"Threlkeld, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Y. Somme, Picardie France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Threlkeld, Cumberland, Eng.":"Threlkeld, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Threlkeld, Cumberland, England